The rape of Jane Doe by a football team of Steubenville, Ohio was going to be pushed under the rug when suddenly a hacktivist group, Anonymous, started doing an investigation. When the authoritative figure of a town is not doing their job is it ok for an outsider to step in. Anonymous threatened the school with disclosing personal information of the people involved int he rape of Jane Doe if nothing was done about the case. This challenges the ethical aspects of hacktivism, while hacktivism in itself serves to better society by exposing wrong doings to the public the means of getting this information is illegal. In this case if the hacktivist group Anonymous did not intervene the football players would have been unaccountable for their actions. This sparked a divide in the small town, more and more people were coming out with their own rape stories and a patterned emerged where people reported rape cases just for the authorities to disregard the reports. Hacktivist events such as this one change society for the better despite the ethical aspects of hacking the outcome of this event lead to the making of a platform where other people can share their rape stories without having to worry about what other people say about them. This case also helped Jane Doe who was not gonna see her rapists behind bars.

In the United States we have a very complicated and thorough justice system. It has many safeguards in place to try and make sure people are innocent until proven guilty. However, crimes can easily fly under the radar and go unpunished if there if no evidence of the crime or if the witnesses involved do not tell the truth. In Steubenville, Ohio, a proud high school football town, a rape case took place that flew under the radar and went unpunished for quite some time. It may have gone unpunished forever, if it were not for the loosely connected hacker group called Anonymous. A member in this group was able to get a hold of a video of a student joking about his two fellow students raping an underage girl among other materials. Because of this video an investigation was eventually launched, and two students were found guilty in juvenile court for raping a minor. A few school administrators were also indicted and charged with various crimes such as hiding evidence or not reporting child abuse. In these types of situations where it seems like nothing will change, is it ethical for an outsider such as anonymous to intervene? To analyze the ethics of this situation we can first explore this situation through a general perspective. Without anonymous bringing light to this issue two criminals would have been able to simply continue their football careers as if nothing happened and a young girl would likely never have got justice for the crimes against her. Since some faculty at the school were complicit and actively tampering with evidence in one case or not reporting child abuse this was not your everyday case. The tampering with evidence and the failure to report by the adults in this situation was completely unethical in itself as they really should have been the ones to put a stop to these events as soon as it crossed their path. It is difficult to argue who is acting more unethically, the adults involved in covering up information about the rape or the hacker group anonymous attaining that video and other material through illegal means. While it does seem that something had to occur in order to bring this criminal act to light and so justice could be served, it’s important to think about the actions that the different members of anonymous took to attain this criminal information and spread it to the public. While in some ways, they are doing something good here, there are laws in place such as the Computer Fraud and Abuse act which punishes some of the actions the different hackers took in this situation. One of the supposed hackers involved named Deric Lostutter was accused of hacking the school’s football website RollRedRoll and displaying some uncovered information on there. Although he has personally denied hacking the site [1], years later he plead guilty to conspiring to hack a website and a second charge of lying to an FBI agent that was investigating the security breach. He was sentenced to two years in prison for these acts. While it is interesting that the charge is only conspiring to hack the website, and not actually hacking the website. In the eyes of the law even conspiring to hack a website is a computer crime and is punishable by law. One thing interesting to note is at first Lostutter was facing up to ten years for the crimes he was accused of, which was even more time than the two rapists were facing [2]. It is most definitely hard to say whether the hackers in anonymous such as Lostutter were acting in the right in these cases or not. Lostutter was the person who obtained and published different tweets and Instagram photos from the incident and people involved and was in a video threat in a mask which was posted by another hacker on the team’s fan page [3]. He was not charged with spreading this information, maybe surprisingly to some. It can be argued though that without the help of Lostutter and the ones who hacked into the football team’s website, this rape case would have never been uncovered. While computer hacking and computer fraud have to be punishable by law because the acts could be so dangerous, it can be argued in a few different ways that sometimes these acts are necessary to bring change or awareness to a certain issue. Say a certain computer vulnerability was used by these hackers to gain access to some of this information in the first place, it can be argued that those vulnerabilities should be exposed to improve security in these computer systems and reduce possible breach points in any system. While exposing security vulnerabilities is undoubtedly important, usually it is recommended to do this in a way that does not cause and damage or any information to be revealed and taken advantage of. This was certainly done in a way where information was compromised and taken elsewhere to be exposed on the internet. This normally should not be okay, however on the other side of the problem is a rape case that possibly would never have been uncovered. It could also be argued that if it weren’t for this hacker group, the kids who raped the girl would possibly have gone on to do other bad things, or simply never had to face justice for an objectively horrible crime. It is important to look at this from the lens of a couple different ethical theories, such as utilitarianism. In this theory, it explains that the most ethical action is the one that provides the most utility, or happiness in a way, to the most people. It seems to me like there is more utility in the action of exposing this information and bringing the 2 kids who engaged in a very horrible crime to justice. Without this event occurring, many women in that community would not have had the courage to speak up about their injustices and past crimes done against them. Whatever security vulnerability that allowed the various hackers to get text messages and Instagram pictures from the people involved, and that allowed the hackers to take over the football team’s website, has now been exposed and can hopefully be patched after those breaches are identified. It can be argued that whatever hardships people faced who lived in the town and whatever hardships they went through due to the division caused by this information coming out, was in fact necessary for the greater good, even though computer hacking laws were broken in some instances. It is hard to simply say just do not break the law, when doing so in this case produced justice for the girl who had to go through such a horrible act being done to her. While it is somewhat dangerous to be the one to expose information yourself, when not knowing if all of it is completely correct, and not allowing law enforcement to do the job they are meant to do, it is clear law enforcement was not going to do anything in this situation without some prodding to say the least. All in all, after considering a theory of ethics in utilitarianism, we can say that in times where things seem like they won’t change, it is acceptable for a hacker group like anonymous to step in and shed light on an issue. Whatever negative aspects come out of a hacker group breaking computer fraud and hacking laws, they are uncovering important information while on the other hand also uncovering certain security vulnerabilities. While it can be dangerous to do vigilante work like this when it isn’t certain what the facts of a situation are, it is clear that at least in this situation the Anonymous members intervened for the greater good of everyone involved. Two rapists were charged and different faculty members who tried to keep the information from going public were also charged. That is a very good positive outcome at whatever cost the hacking had on the town and the people involved.

Abstract Juvenile delinquency is a common social problem facing all countries nowadays. The seriousness and potential danger of the crime has been gradually known by the whole society. The unhealthy social environment and network environment are the root causes of juvenile delinquency. Network environment security and privacy are extremely important. Because people can read a lot of information on the Internet, and the information is transmitted very quickly. Bad online content can easily lead to all kinds of social problems, such as violent behavior and personal injury. Keywords: Juvenile delinquency, Network environment, social problems. Introduction There was a sexual assault in Steubenville, Ohio in the United States. Two high school football players sexually assaulted a high school girl. When the two boys sexually assaulted the girl, there were many classmates nearby. Other onlookers not only did not stop, but also picked up mobile phones to film. But when a teen sexual assault committed by two members of the football team surfaced, the shadowy hacker group Anonymous caught wind of the story and decided to intervene. After publishing videos and social media from the night of the assault to their millions of online followers, they sparked viral outrage and demands for #JusticeforJaneDoe. They unleashed a passionate mob, and their actions divided the small town, but in the process gave strength to generations of women forced to hide abuse. Juvenile delinquency In recent years, juvenile delinquency is on the rise. It is an urgent and important task to prevent and prevent juvenile delinquency. The main characteristics of juvenile delinquency are short experience, shallow experience, simple motive, and purpose. There are many reasons for juveniles to commit crimes, including family, school, society, and themselves. The poor quality of teenagers is the ultimate cause that leads them to commit crimes. Terrible family environment or improper educational methods are important factors leading to juvenile delinquency. Juvenile delinquency is a problem that has existed since ancient times and can often be seen in historical records. “There is even evidence that it dates back to 306 BC since the Romans had special provisions for stealing children in their original laws. The Romans realized that their responsibility for these crimes was limited.” (Kvaraceus, 1964) Juvenile delinquency is very common in modern society, and it is inseparable with the characteristics of teenagers themselves. People's behavior must be determined by psychological and social factors, and it is under this premise that people can act according to their ideas rather than their needs. The causes of juvenile delinquency. First, teenagers are in the transition period from children to adults, and great changes will take place. During this period, teenagers become physically mature, have a stronger sense of personal consciousness and independence, have a strong curiosity and desire to pursue, but lack the ability to control themselves. Second, there are differences in the motives of juveniles and adults. A large part of juvenile delinquency is not for money. They want to prove themselves in some way or commit illegal ACTS while they are not sober. Thirdly, many teenagers are unwilling to do nothing in their life, so they are willing to create conflict. Social problems caused by the Internet If Anonymous had not posted the video online, people would not have reacted so strongly. Crime happens all around us every day, and people read about it in the news. People normally don't get so angry, and the news they see just becomes a topic of discussion. There are other reasons why this has caused so much public anger. Just like the American call "Black lives matter", there are countless examples already happening around us. And this incident has attracted more social attention, so people use this incident to vent their anger. It is wrong to post the route of a crime scene on an online platform. As we can see, the news reports that some of the crime's facts will not be released by video or pictures on the scene of the crime. Even when the facts of the crime are published, they are mosaics. The aim is first to avoid causing discomfort and second to protect privacy. Anonymous is a hacker community, it is not a formal news platform, so the purpose is to make people see the truth. Hacktivism One of the largest hacktivist groups in the world today, is a far reaching organization of hackers around the globe. First appearing in 2008, Anonymous takes their name after the anonymity created by the internet and their desire to remain unknown. As a result, members of the group often do not even know one another outside the internet. Commonly known for launching coordinated attacks. These attacks can be against corporations, individuals and even government institutions and agencies. Their motive is to use hacking to bring about political or social change. Most members prefer total anonymity. Therefore they do not publicly announce their participation within the group. However, some members can be distinguished by their use of the well-known Guy Fawkes mask. This is usually an attempt to hide their identity in public. Hacker attack has always been a problem of computer security, which poses a great security threat to the network. In the early days of the development of the network, people paid more attention to the convenience and availability of the network but ignored the security of the network. In the past, when the network coverage area was very small, the seriousness of the network security problem was not easy to be noticed by people. However, computer network security becomes a problem that cannot be ignored when the key business such as banking is operated on the network, when the main business of enterprises is operated on the network, and when the activities of government departments are increasingly networked. The existence of hackers is very easy to lose important documents and information, causing irreparable losses. The hacker attack is divided into three stages: first, determine the target; Second, collect information related to the attack target, and find out the security vulnerabilities of the system; Third, carry out attacks. Early hackers used only a few tricks to find and fix holes in computer systems. With the development of the Internet, some people find a way to make money from it and start hacking into other people's computers. “Hacking is no longer just about breaking into a computer to steal money or data. Hackers have developed new methods of influencing policy and bringing about change.” (Patrick) Conclusion Juvenile delinquency has become a very common social problem, we need to pay attention to these problems even though. For teenagers, the educational environment and living environment are extremely important, because they can always learn something quickly from the side. In addition, network security is also a key issue of concern. Hacker intrusion has been a very common thing, their existence to the computer network security has brought great hidden danger. There will still be many problems in the development of computers, and we need to deal with them rationally. I hope people can use the network correctly and build a safe network environment together.

A rape case at Steubenville High School in Ohio in 2012 was intervened by the hacker organization Anonymousd. This case became a major case of national concern. The emergence of this incident has raised the public's and national attention to rape cases to an unprecedented height. From this perspective, this is an unprecedented revolution, a great revolution aimed at protecting women. The Steubenville High School rape case encourages more female victims of rape cases to tell their experiences, making the criminals who had been impunity really punished by the law. At the same time, the AA incident made those rape perpetrators or potential perpetrators no longer underestimate the criminal costs and moral hazards brought about by rape. Perhaps they would no longer think that "rape is a small matter" or "I can rape Women escape the punishment of the law", which is a very critical influence, because it will reduce the incidence of rape cases at the source. The most important part, the case brought a storm to the government and judicial system. The Steubenville High School rape case urged the government and judicial institutions to increase their attention to rape cases and intensified their review of rape cases. At the same time, some judicial officials who ignored rape cases and local officials who tried to cover up rape cases were discovered and punished. The U.S. Youth Protection Law and Rape Act also ushered in some new changes. First of all, from the perspective of rape victims, the occurrence of the Steubenville High School rape case has given countless women who are suffering from rape have the confidence to speak out their experience, rather than remain silent. It is like an encouragement, these victims have the power to speak out their experience. Because now they believe that their justice can be done. Compared to before the incident, the rape case has received unprecedented attention, and more people understand that rape is not only an immoral act but also a serious crime. The protection of women's rights is developing in a positive way. The title of this solidarity action is #JusticeforJaneDoe. I think this is a just revolution, but not all revolutions are peaceful. In the documentary, this incident is called a civil war on social media. Revolutions bring justice while also bringing destruction. Residents of the small town believe that they are experiencing cyber violence. The actions of anonymous people and Internet mobs have prevented the residents of the town from living and working normally. They believe that Anonymous has divided their community and damaged the reputation of the town. This incident made the originally peaceful town become the focus of national attention. Many innocent residents have been accused by the Internet. The privacy of more and more town residents is being violated. The justice of the revolution was questioned. From the perspective of consequentialism, the result of this event is just. What determines the justice of war and revolution? A famous example is the American Civil War led by President Lincoln. Many soldiers in the South and North died for this war. But we believe that this war is just because the purpose of the revolution is just and it has got positive results. From a moral point of view, an anonymous person can choose to do nothing. However, perhaps this rape case will be ignored forever. Rather than getting justice done, perhaps we need people to intervene in this incident. As two other important components of this incident: Anonymous and passionate Internet mob. Their appearance changed the development direction of the whole event. Now I want to raise two important questions. the first. Should we regard such behavior of Anonymous as a kind of lynching? Second, must the people's behavior be correct? As we all know, anonymity is to allow users to make some personal comments without using their real names. From an ethical point of view, this is actually an irresponsible behavior. Although anonymous organizations claim that their actions are just, but because their remarks are made anonymously. So in theory, their behavior can easily escape the supervision of the law. Simply put, their behavior is uncontrollable. Uncontrollable behavior often carries the risk of crime. So can an anonymous person’s behavior be forgiven? I think it can. Anonymous persons are like anonymous witnesses. They are under great pressure while providing assistance to the case. These pressures may come from threats from criminals and concerns about personal privacy. Based on this idea, their privacy also needs to be protected, so they choose to remain anonymous to protect their interests. However, the only prerequisite for ensuring that anonymity’s actions are legitimate is that anonymity must voluntarily abide by the corresponding ethical standards and laws. Now that social media has been widely used, anonymous people used the Internet to expose the incident. The emergence of social media made this event spread across the country at an incredible speed. We can call Anonymous’s actions inflammatory. The online exposure of Anonymous has aroused national attention and people’s excitement like a virus. So must the actions of the Internet mobs instigated by anonymous people be correct? I think it is not. Although most of the people provided active help for this event, they participated in solidarity and offline rallies. We can call this part of the people a united social force. However, there are still a small number of emotional Internet users who have excessive behavior. They brought cyber violence. These emotional Internet mobs used illegal and immoral methods to achieve justice. Although they thought that their purpose might be just, they used language to violently attack the residents of the town. In addition, they also used excessive data mining methods to destroy the personal privacy of criminals and innocent residents. This behavior is tantamount to a lynching. The word incitement is often unjust. Therefore, some people believe that Anonymousd should be responsible for inciting online mobs. This view is incorrect. Because the people cannot stay sensible forever. I must mention a famous example: the death of Socrates. Socrates' final trial is often used by modern people as an example of "democratic tyranny". To put it simply, the democracy of the majority may make evil judgments under the wrong guidance. People are herd. Under wrong guidance, people may become emotional and eventually lose their judgment on the physical and intellectual nature of things, making people's behavior lose fairness and justice. There is even a radical view that legal trials have destroyed the normal lives of criminals. Such thinking is truly immoral. There is a view that criminal acts should be handed over to justice and the government for sanctions at any time. The people should not try unjust acts in private. The purpose of people uniting to establish a government is to hope that their rights can be guaranteed. At the same time, the people hand over the rights of trial and supervision to the government and judicial departments, hoping to get a fair result when their rights are violated. But when the judiciary and the government are not doing anything, who should we deliver justice? On the one hand, Anonymous’s intervention is aimed at safeguarding the rights of female victims. This is the purpose of justice. On the other hand, the intervention of Anonymous has caused some damage, but it has brought positive results. Therefore, I think such intervention is moral and a just act. The government and the judiciary should be responsible for the rape case. First of all, I believe that the judicial system and the government should be responsible for monitoring the actions of the anonymous and the people, so that the actions of the anonymous and the people are under control. It is guaranteed that anonymous persons and people are using legal actions to exercise their legitimate rights to achieve justice, because freedom of speech and women rights need the protection of the state. Credibility is vital to the government. The government has the responsibility and obligation to protect the basic rights of the people, not to ignore and indulge criminal acts. Impunity for criminals is shameful and immoral for the government. Criminals must be tried, and judicial personnel who protect criminal acts should be tried.

Activism has existed for decades, but only recently has the internet also become a factor in political participation. Hacktivism is a new method where it takes both hacking and activism to bring change to present conditions where hacking reaches people from all over the world and allow them to participate and be an activist in the issue. Steubenville in Ohio that was once known for its high school sports became infamous when a hacker group known as Anonymous took over and exposed two members of the football team assaulting an underage girl. Steubenville had kept quiet about the incident and protected their star football team, but Anonymous didn’t let it slide as they intervened and published videos and posted on social media to notify their millions of followers about the disturbing event. As the word spread, their millions of followers and more were outraged and demanded for justice. This eventually led to the start of the #MeToo movement where victims of the rape culture that were once ignored or had kept quiet came forward. Incidents involving sexual assaults and other social justice issues are always being disregarded and to understand when it is acceptable for outsiders to intervene is difficult. However, there are a couple ethical aspects that can be used to analyze the video and the ethics of the situation, such as viewing it from different stakeholders’ perspectives: the hacktivists, victims of the situation, the football players, the town of Steubenville and the government, and identifying the impacts of hacktivism on each stakeholder as well as the ethics of hacktivism in itself. To manage ethical problems, one can “list the stakeholders [1]” which are the people and organizations affected. Another way is to “identify responsibilities of the decision maker [2]”and “the impact of the options on the stakeholders [3]”such as the consequences, risks, benefits, harms, and costs. From the perspective of the hacktivists, hacktivism supports their point of view as they are the ones publicly denouncing the attackers through the videos and social media posts. The reason behind their action is morally acceptable as they are hacking to bring awareness and justice to the situation and victims affected. They believe that since there has been countless cases of rape and sexual assault that has never been brought justice and nothing has changed to prevent and punish those who has caused it, they think they have the responsibility to take action since they have the power to do so on the internet. On the contrary, knowing that hacking is illegal, the way they bring light to the matter is unethical hence the mask and the voice changer that protects their identity from the public and government officials. The risk of being a hacktivist includes potentially having their identity revealed which could lead to horrible consequences such as paying fines up to $250,000 and 10 years in jail. For the hacker was “sentenced in a federal courtroom in Kentucky on Wednesday to the maximum of two years in prison by the U.S. District Court Judge Danny Reeves [4]”for his crimes. This shows that with hacktivism comes huge consequences as even though it morally seemed right as Lostutter helped the victim and gave the football players what he personally believes they deserve. From the perspective of the victims, they may see hackers as their guardian angel as someone out there is bringing them justice when they couldn’t do anything themselves. However, without ever directly contacting the victims, the hacktivists will never know whether what they’re doing with the information is what the victims want. In this case, the victims may also despise the hacktivist for sharing their experience with the world as they may not be ready, as Lostutter “exposed the victim in the case to unwanted international attention [5]”. Another perspective are the football players, where hacktivism causes the most damage to them as that is specifically who are targeted from the hacktivism. From an unbiased point of view, everyone makes mistakes and so to be the assaulters from the video is certainly unfortunate as they are penalized and punished far more heavily for their actions than any other attacker that has gotten away with it. From being punished by prosecutors, they also received national humiliation that will follow them for the rest of their lives and ruin any chance of having a good career. Strangers that look at their faces will recognize and associate them with the sexual assault. The town of Steubenville is innocent in the rape case, but because of the rape incident caused by the high school football team, the Steubenville’s name is stained and now anyone who is from there is also looked down upon and loathed on media. From the video, it mentions how they have divided the town, and showed them having rallies of their own to show that they are not ashamed of being from Steubenville. From the perspective of the government, hacktivism is definitely not in their favor as not only does it make them look bad for not putting more effort into making society a better place, it also shows how fragile their security is as individuals can hack and cause data breaches a little too easily. Moreover, their prosecutors and government officials are pressured to react a certain way and be diligent in what they choose as their next action since sensitive issues such as rape can lead to civil war especially if protesting was already happening. Hacktivism in a legal standpoint is unethical and illegal and so Lostutter in this rape case made himself a vigilante by working without legal authority. Moreover, hacktivism is also seen as unethical as the hackers are releasing personal information. In the situation, Lostutter “threatened to reveal personal information of those he accused of improper action [6]”, so unless the football players and the prosecutor complied with his demands and conditions he would release the information which is blackmail. Eventually, “Jefferson County Prosecutor Jane Hanlin recused herself from the rape case investigation at an early stage and turned it over to state officials [7]”so her and her family could leave town because Lostutter was making threats against her and her family. Hanlin also mentioned that the rape case investigation “had been fully investigated, appropriate charges had been filed and the attorney general of the state of Ohio had publicly stated there was no cover-up of any sort [8]”.From that, it was known that “the case was actually receiving more than adequate coverage in the press [9]”,so what Lostutter did was extremely unnecessary. On the other hand, despite hacking not being legal, the reason behind the action is moral as it shows that it was actually time for someone to do something about it, as though charges were made, it was also quickly swept under the media and everyone was moving on from it without making a change to address rape culture as a whole. For instance, the lady in the video says “it is hard to actually even get anybody in this area to discuss rape and if they do, it’s kind of a little bit and then it’s like ok, I’ve had enough, put the subject away [10]”10 showing that it was time for outsiders to intervene. In conclusion, there are several different ethical aspects to view the Stuebenville rape case from where each stakeholder carries a different perspective and the effects of hacktivism also differs for each one of them. For the hacktivists, they believe the justice they bring from hacktivism outweighs the unethicality of it, and if the victims condone them sharing their experience, they would also believe hacktivism is morally acceptable. On the contrary, the football players, the town of Steubenville and the government would be against it because it damages their reputations and would have to face repercussions. All in all, despite negative views about hacktivism, it is definitely needed when nothing changes after a couple incidents and when society makes it a habit to simply cover it on media just for the sake of coverage but not doing anything truly to stop the occurrence of it.
